<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-08-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-08-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="1330" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1330">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/15664.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Mine and Smelter Operators
                                Association</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-08-06">
                                    <hi rend="italic">August 6, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Department negotiating to have meeting of mining men in Chihuahua
                            postponed. Meantime, in order that quick action may be <pb facs="1050" n="934" xml:id="pg_934"/> taken in case necessity, your members
                            should keep in close touch with Mr. Carothers and await outcome
                            negotiations.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>